casebody.data:
Jeffrey SCOTT, Appellant,
v.
DIVISION OF EMPLOYMENT SECURITY, Respondent. WD 81642 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: March 5, 2019 Jeffrey Scott, Kansas City, MO, Appellant Acting Pro Se. Bruce Farmer, Jefferson City, MO, Counsel for Respondent. Before Division Four: Karen King Mitchell, Chief Judge Presiding, Thomas N. Chapman, Judge, and Cory L. Atkins, Visiting Judge

ORDER

Per Curiam:

Jeffrey Scott appeals the Decision of the Labor and Industrial Relations Commission finding that he was disqualified from receiving unemployment benefits because he voluntarily quit his job without good cause. Scott argues that the evidence demonstrates he was improperly discharged for misconduct. We affirm the Commission's decision. Rule 84.16(b).
